    <item>
      <title>Design an API Rate Limiter — Introduction</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/learning/advanced-skills/system-design-practice/intermediate-systems/3_api-rate-limiter/0_introduction/1_introduction/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/learning/advanced-skills/system-design-practice/intermediate-systems/3_api-rate-limiter/0_introduction/1_introduction/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;1-what-is-a-rate-limiter&#34;&gt;1. What is a Rate Limiter?&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A Rate Limiter is a system that &lt;strong&gt;controls how many requests a client can make within a given time window&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;It is used to protect backend systems from:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;excessive traffic&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;abuse (e.g., bots, brute-force attacks)&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;accidental overload&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h3 id=&#34;example&#34;&gt;Example&lt;/h3&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;Allow 100 requests per user per minute&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;If a user exceeds this limit:&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; style=&#34;color:#f8f8f2;background-color:#272822;-moz-tab-size:4;-o-tab-size:4;tab-size:4;-webkit-text-size-adjust:none;&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-text&#34; data-lang=&#34;text&#34;&gt;&lt;span style=&#34;display:flex;&#34;&gt;&lt;span&gt;→ Reject further requests (HTTP 429 Too Many Requests)&#xA;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;h2 id=&#34;2-why-rate-limiting-matters&#34;&gt;2. Why Rate Limiting Matters&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;hr&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;In real-world systems, uncontrolled traffic can lead to:&lt;/p&gt;</description>
